# When asked to code a task
When you are asked to code a task from [implementation-tasks.mdc](mdc:.cursor/specifications/implementation-tasks.mdc):
1. Review the @main-project-specifications.mdc
2. Identify the task in @implementation-tasks.mdc
3. Write the code
4. Ensure proper module dependencies are declared
5. Compile with `mvn clean verify`
6. Run unit tests with `mvn test`
7. Mark the task with an "x", example:`- [x] example task`
8. Commit changes